review.reviewBody: I'm originally from the eastern US. For all the amazing food in this city, I've have had a difficult time finding a General Tso's Chicken in Vancouver that hits all the same notes as what I ate growing up. After trying several places and being disappointed, Deer Lake Wonton House's General Tso's Chicken & Rice was pure nostalgia! Sweet, spicy, garlicky, with just the right amount of ginger and sauce. Don't sleep on the Pork Dumpling (10 pcs ) either---super yummy filling, not-too-doughy but still tender, and a nice chili oil-based sauce too. Classic stuff---I'll definitely be ordering from here again.
Combination D was awesome. Everything was fresh, hot and tasty.  I will definitely be coming back 😋😋😋
Food was as good as usual, however portion sizes seem to have taken a hitbandnthe chicken balls were more like nuggets than balls. Was weird.
